Sure! In C programming, an if/then statement is used to execute a block of code conditionally based on a specified condition. Here's an example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
}
```

In this example, the if statement checks if the age variable is greater than or equal to 18. If the condition is true, the code inside the curly braces will be executed. If the condition is false, the code inside the curly braces will not be executed.

You can also use an else statement to execute a block of code if the condition is false:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
  // Code to execute if the condition is false
}
```

In this example, if the age variable is less than 18, the code inside the else statement will be executed.
